SEQUENCING PROTOCOL ID (Required): A unique ID for the protocol.
SEQUENCING PROTOCOL NAME: A short name for the protocol.
SEQUENCING PROTOCOL DESCRIPTION: A general description of the protocol.
PUBLICATION DOI: The publication digital object identifier (doi) for the protocol.
PROTOCOLS.IO DOI: The protocols.io digital object identifier (doi) for the protocol.
DOCUMENT FILENAME: A filename of a PDF document containing the details of the protocol.
INSTRUMENT MANUFACTURER AND MODEL (Requi: A term that may be associated with a instrument-related ontology term.
INSTRUMENT MANUFACTURER AND MODEL ONTOLO: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
LOCAL MACHINE NAME: Local name for the particular machine used for sequencing.
PAIRED END (Required): Whether the sequenced molecule was sequenced from both ends.
SEQUENCING METHOD (Required): A term that may be associated with a process-related ontology term.
SEQUENCING METHOD ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
SEQUENCING METHOD ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOG: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
FASTQ CREATION METHOD: Method used for the generation of fastq files from bcl files.
FASTQ CREATION METHOD VERSION: Version of the program used for fastq generation.
POOLED CHANNELS: The number of channels pooled within a sequencing lane.
DROP UNIFORMITY: Whether drop uniformity was achieved as a result of visual inspection of emulsion after a 10x run.
